irected percolation. We\nfind that the transition between these exponents is governed by a competition\nbetween merging and propagation of activity, and identify an appropriate\nscaling relationship for the transition point. Finally, we show that commonly\nused measures, such as the branching ratio and dynamic susceptibility, fail to\nestablish criticality in the absence of time-scale separation calling for a\nreanalysis of criticality in the brain.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 22 Aug 2019 01:27:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 8 Oct 2020 19:24:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-23"}
