 flaring gamma-ray\nblazar TXS 0506+056 in September 2017. We'll present the H.E.S.S. observations\nobtained within ~4h hours of the neutrino detection as well as a complementary\nsearch for gamma-ray emission at longer timescales and put them into the\nmulti-wavelength and multi-messenger context.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 22 Aug 2019 13:35:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-23"}
